Package: multifer
Title: Typed Perturbation Inference for Projector-Based Multivariate Models
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person(given = "Bradley",
           family = "Buchsbaum",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "brad.buchsbaum@gmail.com")
Description: A typed perturbation inference platform for latent-root
    multivariate models. Ships mature support for PCA-family one-block
    variance inference and covariance-mode two-block methods (PLSC-family),
    qualified support for canonical-correlation models, and architectural
    slots for planned generalized-eigen and predictive-cross engines. Built
    around typed shapes (geometry, relation, design), strict dispatch,
    machine-enforced validity contracts, latent-unit output schemas, and
    a clean separation between permutation-based significance and
    bootstrap-based stability.
